.TH "wait_for_cmd_complete" 9 "wait_for_cmd_complete" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wait_for_cmd_complete \- waits for a command to complete.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" wait_for_cmd_complete
.BI "(void __iomem *addr "  ","
.BI "u64 busy_bit "  ","
.BI "int bit_state "  ","
.BI "bool may_sleep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
address
.IP "busy_bit" 12
bit to check for busy
.IP "bit_state" 12
state to check
.IP "may_sleep" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function that waits for a command to Write into RMAC
ADDR DATA registers to be completed and returns either success or
error depending on whether the command was complete or not.
Return value:
SUCCESS on success and FAILURE on failure.
